Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.61,0:00:04.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Friendship! Romance! Mystery!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.41,0:00:05.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We try our best because we've made those promises!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.41,0:00:08.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Three beautiful suspects in kimonos!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.24,0:00:09.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's solve the mystery of the mole on the breast!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.16,0:00:11.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.66,0:00:13.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the body of a child and the brain of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.37,0:00:15.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.26,0:01:52.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Th There's no murder weapon?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.35,0:01:54.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.35,0:01:57.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm shocked. You haven't even found the murder weapon yet
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.94,0:01:59.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll let you get back to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.81,0:02:00.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, wait a minute please.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.27,0:02:05.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We still want to interview you all eventually, so can you wait in a different room?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.65,0:02:08.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well if you're telling us to wait, I guess we wait
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.49,0:02:10.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But as for me, I'm not answering any questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.37,0:02:14.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're in no position to be suspecting us.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.91,0:02:18.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're treating us like culprits when all we did was use the outdoor bath. I can't believe it
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.08,0:02:19.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Outdoor bath?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.13,0:02:24.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it seems they went in at around the time of the crime, 11:50 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.09,0:02:28.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And around 20 minutes after that, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} went in.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.22,0:02:30.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? You went in?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.39,0:02:34.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me you were peeking into the woman's bath!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.26,0:02:35.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was mixed bathing!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.68,0:02:39.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I see. But how is your saying it was mixed bathing an excuse?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.27,0:02:43.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because, you see, I think if anyone went in they'd be just as lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.77,0:02:44.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah-re-re.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.32,0:02:47.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't this a movie that Kazuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was in?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.11,0:02:50.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would something like that be here?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.82,0:02:52.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a video that Kamoshita{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} rented.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.24,0:02:55.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This inn has videos of movies available for rental.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.33,0:02:57.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, gimme that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.71,0:03:00.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let me check this out.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.63,0:03:03.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.63,0:03:05.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you really have the time to be checking that out?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.75,0:03:09.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who knows, maybe there's some kind of clue hidden in the movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.68,0:03:14.64,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Pun: The word for staircase (kaidan) in the title is pronounced the same as the word for ghost stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.02,0:03:19.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Somehow this feels like its going to be a scary movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.10,0:03:21.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heh, it's just the usual kid's stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.27,0:03:24.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, it'll be OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.36,0:03:27.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no way your mother was the culprit
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.36,0:03:30.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not really worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.57,0:03:31.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About that woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.70,0:03:38.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.20,0:03:40.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That sound reminds me of my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.41,0:03:42.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, hold on...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.47,0:03:51.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.13,0:03:55.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One of the guests suddenly called to say they wanted a late night meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.51,0:03:57.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was the noise bothering you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.64,0:03:58.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.18,0:04:02.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, Kazuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, you really do want to see your mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.52,0:04:03.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.98,0:04:07.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It just thought it might have been a clue that could lead us to finding her.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.07,0:04:10.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, idiot! Behind you! Behind you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.49,0:04:12.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I said behind you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.70,0:04:14.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.28,0:04:16.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's something on the ceiling! Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.25,0:04:22.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're really into it, those two.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.67,0:04:34.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was kinda fun, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.43,0:04:36.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, not bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.60,0:04:39.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that didn't tell us anything important.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.93,0:04:40.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nope.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.27,0:04:43.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now I see, that's what it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.77,0:04:48.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why after strangling him...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.31,0:04:51.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit put the body in the bathtub and got it wet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.53,0:04:53.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are two mysteries remaining.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.70,0:04:57.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason the culprit went to take a bath, and that mole.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.62,0:05:01.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She may have gotten naked in order to take her victim off his guard.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.41,0:05:03.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what's with that mole?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.04,0:05:05.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Yokomizo, have a second?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.29,0:05:07.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.79,0:05:12.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We were so preoccupied with the marks on his neck that we didn't notice it before, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.84,0:05:16.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are signs that the victim was struck several times on the back of his head.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.26,0:05:19.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he was beaten to death?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.80,0:05:20.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.68,0:05:23.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was some bleeding, but the wounds weren't fatal.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.89,0:05:27.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Most likely he was strangled after he was struck unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.56,0:05:32.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's the case, the weapon might have been that shower nozzle.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.19,0:05:35.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please check it right away for a luminol reaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.90,0:05:36.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.24,0:05:38.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's how it happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.24,0:05:42.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then the suspicious person was the one hiding this. That person!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.91,0:05:45.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,OK, time to put Uncle to sleep with the tranquilizer gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.91,0:05:47.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.04,0:05:47.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.62,0:05:48.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't give me "Eh?"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.96,0:05:51.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's already past three o'clock. You need to go to bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.67,0:05:52.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.21,0:05:57.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because tomorrow we need to find Kazuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s mother. It seems she's a good cook.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.72,0:05:59.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A good cook?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.22,0:05:59.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.18,0:06:03.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} told us he often fell asleep while looking at his mother's mole, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.31,0:06:08.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems he remembers hearing the rhythmic sound of a knife chopping at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.94,0:06:10.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's proof that she's was a good cook, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.40,0:06:12.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, right
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.15,0:06:15.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll be coming right away, so go ahead and spread out my futon.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.82,0:06:16.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.03,0:06:20.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, if Kazuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} wakes up will you tell him something?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.74,0:06:25.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Your mother is no murderer."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.16,0:06:30.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Yokomizo! There was a luminol reaction from the shower nozzle.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.38,0:06:36.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as we thought, the culprit struck Kamoshita{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} unconscious with the shower nozzle and then strangled him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.96,0:06:42.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so? Have you found the crucial thin, long, black string that strangled him?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.89,0:06:49.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, as for that, we searched all the places where those three suspects could have hidden it, but it wasn't there
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.60,0:06:55.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then that means one of those three might still have the murder weapon with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.03,0:06:59.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,OK, we'll have a female officer give those three a physical inspection.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.99,0:07:02.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think that would be pointless.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.91,0:07:03.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.78,0:07:04.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.12,0:07:09.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There that picture that Kamoshita{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} took with his cellphone as he was being killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.75,0:07:14.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The female culprit in the picture has a mole on the left side of her chest!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.63,0:07:17.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Kunano{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s mole is on her right side.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.80,0:07:19.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bessho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s is on her left cheek.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.97,0:07:22.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saegusa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s is on the back of her neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.39,0:07:24.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Obviously none of them are the culprit
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.60,0:07:28.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you go ahead and give them a physical examination anyway, won't that just make them angry?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.81,0:07:33.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But those three are the only employees at this inn who don't have an alibi
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.15,0:07:37.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, that's enough for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.90,0:07:42.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow we can re-examine everybody, including all the guests of the inn.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.66,0:07:46.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure I hit him. What the heck could have happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.03,0:07:50.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like there are some out-of-season mosquitoes here or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.29,0:07:51.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? Mosquitoes?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.37,0:07:55.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, just now I felt on the back of my neck...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.09,0:07:57.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.68,0:08:07.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's appeared! Sleeping Kogoro!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.43,0:08:10.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's finally becoming resistant to it
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.81,0:08:18.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, Inspector Yokomizo, can you please ready the things I'm going to tell you about and bring the three suspects here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.40,0:08:19.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.78,0:08:21.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then you've figured it out, haven't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.74,0:08:29.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. I'll tell you the truth behind the incident where Kamoshita{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was strangled in this room's bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.45,0:08:34.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just like always. What he's saying now is completely different from what he said just before.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.00,0:08:38.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understand, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.34,0:08:42.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,OK, the preparations are all complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.34,0:08:46.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let the Sleeping Kogoro Deduction Show begin!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.06,0:08:57.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, just a minute here! Why did you have to summon us all again'
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.69,0:08:59.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't you see before?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.44,0:09:02.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,None of us have a mole on our chest like the culprit!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.57,0:09:05.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides which, have you found the murder weapon?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.95,0:09:08.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't prove who the murder is without it
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.99,0:09:13.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course we've found it! Right, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.75,0:09:14.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nope.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.46,0:09:15.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We haven't found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.79,0:09:20.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That murder weapon has probably already been disposed of.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.71,0:09:22.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Di-Disposed of? Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.13,0:09:28.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you can find out what the culprit used to strangle Kamoshita{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.84,0:09:30.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By using this screwdriver.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.27,0:09:34.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For some reason it looks like your hand has gotten smaller.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.27,0:09:37.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, don't worry about such trivial details.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.77,0:09:40.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, I've rented it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.77,0:09:41.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.36,0:09:47.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, shall we compare the two?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.32,0:09:51.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This video that Kamoshita{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} rented from the inn.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.58,0:09:55.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And a video of the same movie that's been rented from a video rental store.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.87,0:10:01.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, let's begin with the video from this room that Kamoshita{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} rented.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.01,0:10:12.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just like we saw earlier, there's an eerie opening.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.85,0:10:15.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,OK, next the one from the video rental store.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.10,0:10:17.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? That's far enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.85,0:10:18.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.95,0:10:35.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's the video company's spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.29,0:10:39.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the movie company's spot
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.79,0:10:41.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? Hey now!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.04,0:10:44.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also there's...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.50,0:10:45.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A movie prologue?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.88,0:10:49.80,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Come, let me tell you a story about a cursed school...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.88,0:10:49.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.22,0:10:53.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The previous video started right at the opening title.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.64,0:10:55.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was cut
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.31,0:10:57.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's approximately one minute shorter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.36,0:11:04.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that the culprit could create the murder weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.07,0:11:07.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I see. It was a video tape!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.69,0:11:11.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit opened the cassette with a screwdriver and took out the tape inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.41,0:11:13.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And after cutting of a length to use as the murder weapon...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.95,0:11:17.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They reattached it with cellophane tape or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.62,0:11:21.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If they reattached it so that when it was rewound it would start at the opening title...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.04,0:11:24.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Afterwards, even if the police watched the video...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.67,0:11:26.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They wouldn't suspect anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.71,0:11:32.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, but, the black string in that picture was thinner, more like a kite string
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.39,0:11:34.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's simple enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.35,0:11:38.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, could you take apart the new video cassette that Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} told you to buy for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.61,0:11:53.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, please look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.28,0:11:59.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we do nothing, it just a regular black band; but, if we twist-twist-twist it like this, it becomes...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.79,0:12:01.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.83,0:12:04.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It doesn't look much like a kite string
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.42,0:12:06.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah. You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.59,0:12:09.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't twist it, just stretch it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.09,0:12:11.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Stretch it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.84,0:12:13.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That'll hardly...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.89,0:12:22.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly. If you pull strong enough on a video tape it becomes thin like a kite string.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.10,0:12:28.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Incidentally, the length of a standard video tape is around 30 centimeters for every 10 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.65,0:12:30.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One minute is a meter and 80 centimeters.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.78,0:12:33.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you stretch it, it can easily pass two meters.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.11,0:12:36.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wind it firmly around both hands...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.24,0:12:39.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it will be plenty long enough to strangle someone across the neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.41,0:12:41.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I'm surprised you figured it out
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.75,0:12:44.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How'd you know the video was one minute short?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.00,0:12:49.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By looking at the recording length written on the video box.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.63,0:12:51.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! Where did you come from, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.13,0:12:57.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look! Even though it says 94 minutes on here, earlier when we finished watching the video counter said...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.39,0:12:59.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only one hour and 33 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.35,0:13:01.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Uncle?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.35,0:13:05.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how would they have gotten rid of that video tape earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.19,0:13:11.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Probably they burned it with a lighter or something and flushed the ashes down the drain in the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.36,0:13:15.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Video tapes are made of highly flammable materials.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.70,0:13:19.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm sure I'm not mistaken in saying the murder weapon was the video tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.78,0:13:24.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you inspect the video cassette, you should see signs that it was reattached.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.29,0:13:29.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit placed the body in the bathtub to conceal the fact that she used that as the murder weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.09,0:13:34.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't to confuse the presumed time of death?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.51,0:13:36.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.43,0:13:38.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At your left hand that held the video tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.76,0:13:42.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this? These black marks?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.64,0:13:47.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the magnetic substance that's placed on the surface of the video tape in order to record the images.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.31,0:13:55.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When she washed away the black marks that got on Kamoshita{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s neck when she strangled him, his robe got wet
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.07,0:13:59.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to conceal that, she placed the body in the bathtub.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.12,0:14:07.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But at that time the culprit neglected to wash off something she needed to erase even more.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.54,0:14:10.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The conclusive piece of evidence. That red mole!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.04,0:14:14.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,R-Red? You're not saying the mole in that picture was...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.88,0:14:17.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it wasn't a mole.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.63,0:14:21.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was something that splashed on her when she beat Kamoshita{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} unconscious with the shower nozzle.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.43,0:14:24.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kamoshita{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s blood!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.93,0:14:27.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I see now!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.48,0:14:31.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because of the roughness of the image, that means the darkened spot looked like a mole.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.27,0:14:36.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the reason the culprit got naked was so she wouldn't get blood on her clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.78,0:14:37.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.78,0:14:43.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why when the culprit came into the room, she said she wanted to take a shower and went into the bathroom
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.53,0:14:48.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then she lured him into the bathroom by saying the shower was broken or some other suitable excuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.12,0:14:52.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When he came in, she struck him unconscious with the nozzle.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.84,0:14:56.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, without wasting time putting on her clothes, she cut off some tape from the cassette
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.71,0:15:00.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And she used it to strangle Kamoshita{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.47,0:15:03.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She didn't realize he'd taken that picture at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.10,0:15:06.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then she washed off most of the blood...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.85,0:15:11.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, leaving the room, the culprit returned the scissors and screwdriver used in the crime to their former places.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.23,0:15:16.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then in order to completely wash off the magnetic substance on her hands and the blood...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.69,0:15:18.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She went to the outdoor bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.90,0:15:20.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did I get any part of that wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.78,0:15:22.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one trying who tried to hid her red mole.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.16,0:15:24.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bessho Toshiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.74,0:15:28.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-Tried to hide?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.33,0:15:32.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is ridiculous! Didn't Bessho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} show you right at the beginning? There's no mole on her chest!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.83,0:15:35.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly. That's where I caught on.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.84,0:15:40.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That someone with a reserved personality like Bessho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} would do such a bold thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.88,0:15:44.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I realized that right below the collarbone is a blind spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.64,0:15:50.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Possibly the culprit didn't even realize she had blood on her chest until she saw that photograph.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.06,0:15:51.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You see?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.98,0:15:55.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, she didn't have any blood on her chest!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.81,0:15:59.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course not, because it would have been washed off when she was in the bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.69,0:16:02.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But we should find traces of it if we give her a physical inspection.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.95,0:16:06.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was afraid of that, and so that that section wasn't seen, Bessho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.70,0:16:12.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Concealed it with her hand when she exposed her chest to let the police ascertain that there was no mole on it
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.79,0:16:15.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And to protect against them doing a physical inspection.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.25,0:16:24.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that we wouldn't discover what had stuck to her inner robe when she put her kimono on —\hKamoshita{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s blood!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.64,0:16:25.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.26,0:16:28.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, you're the one"?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.81,0:16:33.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though you're Kazuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s mother, you're the one who blackmailed Kazuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s production company.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.69,0:16:36.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.69,0:16:39.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was just a prank.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.36,0:16:41.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A prank?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.65,0:16:43.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was probably because I was jealous.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.74,0:16:46.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I really wanted to have a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.66,0:16:47.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean you...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.08,0:16:50.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'm not his mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.74,0:16:52.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What I said about his father being a murderer was a lie too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.62,0:16:59.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought that if I threatened them with that, the company wouldn't give Kazuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} any more of his mother's postcards.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.92,0:17:03.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But shortly thereafter they really transferred the money to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.76,0:17:07.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While I was worrying about what do to, that Kamoshita man came sniffing around.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.68,0:17:11.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Should I call him in his room and tell him the truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.27,0:17:13.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Should I say it was a lie?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.14,0:17:16.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But then, he was laughing when he said...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.11,0:17:23.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mother, I understand you feeling you need to protect you son, but this is business.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.69,0:17:28.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well even if I assume that was untrue, now it's my turn to threaten you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.49,0:17:31.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll be squeezing you for the rest of your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.83,0:17:33.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That scared me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.50,0:17:35.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really scared me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.83,0:17:39.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, those details about Kazuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} and his mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.50,0:17:41.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How do you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.71,0:17:45.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll talk about that with the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.51,0:17:50.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Mr. Inspector, I don't regret it or anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.18,0:17:53.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The feelings of a woman who wants children but can't have them...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.52,0:17:57.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I made him understand that for just a bit
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.40,0:18:03.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.07,0:18:06.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then the culprit was Bessho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.53,0:18:13.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Uncle Kogoro said he was going to the Shizuoka Prefectural Police Station for the questioning.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.37,0:18:17.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said he left his wallet so you can take us kids home by train.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.79,0:18:18.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.08,0:18:20.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Where's Kazuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.92,0:18:24.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, he's already changed clothes and gone out to the lobby.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.71,0:18:25.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He says he's ready to go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.05,0:18:26.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.09,0:18:29.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's not going to keep looking for his mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.47,0:18:31.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I guess he's not planning to.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.51,0:18:36.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He had a strange look on his face before he went to bed last night and he wouldn't answer anything I asked him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.98,0:18:40.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder if it's because instead of holding him, I just carried him on my back.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.73,0:18:43.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, you said that, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.82,0:18:46.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That Kazuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s mother wasn't the murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.99,0:18:47.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.61,0:18:50.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does that mean you know who Kazuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s mother is?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.20,0:18:56.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.79,0:18:59.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My, thank you! I'll treasure it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.62,0:19:00.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.75,0:19:01.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.92,0:19:03.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And one more for my grandchild.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.05,0:19:08.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't being held, but being carried on her back?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.22,0:19:14.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. You remember that when he fell asleep while looking at his mother's mole, he heard the sound of a kitchen knife?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.72,0:19:17.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If she was holding him she couldn't have been cooking.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.60,0:19:18.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.93,0:19:22.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Possibly when Kazuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was held when he was brought up at that church.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.69,0:19:25.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so he was mistaken about the mole being on her chest
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.52,0:19:28.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then you mean his mother is the one with the mole on the back of her neck?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.74,0:19:29.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saegusa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.87,0:19:37.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But wasn't she acting awfully cold and aloof?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.83,0:19:41.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She acted that way deliberately so he wouldn't realize she was his mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.75,0:19:45.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think there might have been trouble if Kazuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} found out
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.92,0:19:50.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Possibly Saegusa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had talked about it with the culprit, Bessho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.47,0:19:55.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About how she reluctantly left her own child in the care of a church, and about how cute he was.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.10,0:20:03.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think Bessho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} linked that with the postcards Saegusa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} wrote each month to Kazuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} and knew she was his mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.60,0:20:05.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason the postcards kept coming until the winter of last year was...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.15,0:20:09.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Possibly that Bessho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} made her threat around that time...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.28,0:20:12.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the company stopped giving him the postcards that arrived after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.49,0:20:14.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Er, that's what Uncle Kogoro said!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.87,0:20:18.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how do you know she left him reluctantly?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.24,0:20:25.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the son you wrote postcards to each month were to appear right in front of you, normally you would rush to embrace him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.42,0:20:27.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But because Kazuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} is rich and famous...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.09,0:20:31.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She had to crush those feelings and pretend not to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.26,0:20:34.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doesn't that make you think she must really care about Kazuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.72,0:20:36.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, you're right
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.06,0:20:38.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.31,0:20:42.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyhow, I'm going to go tell that to Kazuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.81,0:20:45.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'd be a shame if he kept on being bitter about his mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.65,0:20:50.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, in truth he's wanted to see his mother desperately.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.65,0:20:53.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That his mother's postcards were all worn out and covered in stains is...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.99,0:20:56.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The evidence that he was crying as he read and re-read them countless times.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.82,0:21:00.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what's more, Kazuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} probably already knows who his mother is.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.83,0:21:03.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, don't you want one too, Saegusa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.33,0:21:04.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.00,0:21:06.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you being so shy for?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.83,0:21:10.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't you the one who watches Kazuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s movies and videos over and over?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.13,0:21:13.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.05,0:21:17.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I won't do one for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.27,0:21:23.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.56,0:21:25.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here, take these.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.27,0:21:30.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you don't send them to me, I'll be back.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.82,0:21:38.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, Kazuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.92,0:21:48.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Forgive me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.67,0:21:51.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Forgive me, Ka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.67,0:21:53.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Forgive me...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.63,0:23:24.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Three days later Kazuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s commission fee arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.60,0:23:25.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wha! Wha!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.22,0:23:29.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this!?!?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.52,0:23:32.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heh, no matter how you look at it, it's a piggy bank.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.02,0:23:34.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,D-Don't tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.82,0:23:41.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess stars don't always earn a lot
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.36,0:23:46.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see, let's see. I knew it, this doesn't even cover my traveling expenses!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.05,0:23:58.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! He's walking!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.97,0:24:02.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's amazing... He's walking.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.89,0:24:08.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no way! How can he do that!?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.99,0:24:21.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wind (Kaze)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.78,0:24:25.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Both the Conan movie and TV show will have started!
